# Session Start Protocol

NOTE: alwaysApply:true has a known bug in Cursor 3.0.16+ where it silently downgrades to requestable. If this rule did not auto-load, manually run: @CONTEXT.md @contaxt files/PLAN.md at the start of the session before any other task.

---

## STEP 0 — READ BEFORE TOUCHING ANYTHING

1. Read CONTEXT.md — full project context, locked decisions, current state
2. Read contaxt files/PLAN.md — current phase, current session deliverable, what comes next

State the current phase and today's session deliverable explicitly before writing any code:
"Today's session will build [X]. It will write to [Supabase tables / site path]. It is run.py step [NAME]."

---

## CANONICAL PIPELINE ORDER — NEVER DEVIATE

run.py STEPS (exact, fixed, immutable):
fx → cot → inr → vol → oi → rr → merge → text → macro → ai → substack → html → validate → deploy

- Never reorder these steps
- Never suggest parallelization
- Never make steps conditional
- New pipelines are added to CANONICAL_ORDER only with explicit instruction
- If user asks to reorder: push back. Only proceed if user types "override canonical order"

---

## PROTECTED DIRECTORIES — NEVER TOUCH

- data/          → bulk output, never read or reference
- briefs/        → generated briefs, never read or reference
- runs/          → pipeline run logs, never read or reference
- _docs/         → Obsidian vault, NEVER modify, NEVER read, NEVER touch
- .venv/         → virtual environment, never modify

---

## PROJECT BOUNDARIES

- Python only. No C++. No Node.js backend. No JavaScript frameworks.
- site/ is static HTML/CSS/JS only. No React. No bundlers.
- All persistent data goes to Supabase. Not local files in production.
- One file per signal module. Do not combine pipeline logic.
- No new dependencies without explicit approval.

---

## BEFORE WRITING ANY CODE

- [ ] CONTEXT.md read and confirmed
- [ ] contaxt files/PLAN.md read and confirmed
- [ ] Session deliverable stated explicitly
- [ ] No conflict with existing Supabase schema
- [ ] No existing script does what you are about to build

